## Ruby & Rails Files

### Models

**File naming:**
- **Singular, snake_case**: `user.rb`, `blog_post.rb`, `article_comment.rb`

**Class naming:**
- **Singular, PascalCase**: `User`, `BlogPost`, `ArticleComment`

**Table naming:**
- **Plural, snake_case**: `users`, `blog_posts`, `article_comments`

```ruby
# Good
class BlogPost < ApplicationRecord
end
# File: app/models/blog_post.rb
# Table: blog_posts

# Bad
class Blogpost < ApplicationRecord
end
# File: app/models/blogpost.rb  # Wrong!
```

### Controllers

**File naming:**
- **Plural, snake_case, ends with `_controller.rb`**: `users_controller.rb`, `blog_posts_controller.rb`

**Class naming:**
- **Plural, PascalCase, ends with `Controller`**: `UsersController`, `BlogPostsController`

```ruby
# Good
class BlogPostsController < ApplicationController
end
# File: app/controllers/blog_posts_controller.rb

# Bad
class BlogPostController < ApplicationController  # Wrong! Should be plural
end
```

### Views

**Directory:**
- **Plural, snake_case**: `app/views/users/`, `app/views/blog_posts/`

**Files:**
- **Action name, snake_case**: `index.html.erb`, `show.html.erb`, `edit.html.erb`

**Partials:**
- **Start with underscore**: `_form.html.erb`, `_blog_post.html.erb`, `_user_card.html.erb`

```
# Good structure
app/views/blog_posts/
├── index.html.erb
├── show.html.erb
├── new.html.erb
├── edit.html.erb
├── _form.html.erb          # Partial
└── _blog_post.html.erb     # Partial
```

### Jobs (Solid Queue)

**File naming:**
- **snake_case, ends with `_job.rb`**: `article_notification_job.rb`, `data_export_job.rb`

**Class naming:**
- **PascalCase, ends with `Job`**: `ArticleNotificationJob`, `DataExportJob`

```ruby
# Good
class ArticleNotificationJob < ApplicationJob
end
# File: app/jobs/article_notification_job.rb
```

### Channels (Solid Cable)

**File naming:**
- **snake_case, ends with `_channel.rb`**: `comments_channel.rb`, `notifications_channel.rb`

**Class naming:**
- **PascalCase, ends with `Channel`**: `CommentsChannel`, `NotificationsChannel`

```ruby
# Good
class CommentsChannel < ApplicationCable::Channel
end
# File: app/channels/comments_channel.rb
```

### Mailers

**File naming:**
- **snake_case, ends with `_mailer.rb`**: `user_mailer.rb`, `article_mailer.rb`

**Class naming:**
- **PascalCase, ends with `Mailer`**: `UserMailer`, `ArticleMailer`

```ruby
# Good
class ArticleMailer < ApplicationMailer
end
# File: app/mailers/article_mailer.rb
```

